WEBVTT

00:00.005 --> 00:01.642
<i>Previously on Devious Maids...</i>

00:02.203 --> 00:04.800
I saw you kissing Dr. Sanders
in the street.

00:04.886 --> 00:07.185
I was supportive when you first gave
your power of attorney to Lucinda

00:07.186 --> 00:09.484
because I thought she had
your best interests at heart.

00:09.519 --> 00:11.578
My father kicked me out
of this house because of you.

00:11.913 --> 00:13.574
I don't want her to leave.

00:14.034 --> 00:14.818
It's Didi.

00:14.818 --> 00:16.654
I wish she was the one
going away.

00:16.688 --> 00:18.322
An opportunity
might present itself.

00:18.356 --> 00:19.490
What's wrong?

00:19.524 --> 00:21.358
There's a problem
with my kidneys.

00:21.393 --> 00:23.994
Seems the little buggers
are starting to shut down.

00:24.029 --> 00:25.863
Sounds like she's more
than a boss to you.

00:25.897 --> 00:27.531
So much more.

00:27.565 --> 00:29.366
I'm moving out tonight.

00:29.401 --> 00:31.869
I'm really sorry
that we couldn't be friends.

00:31.903 --> 00:34.004
- He knows.
- He suspects.

00:34.039 --> 00:36.373
- You think they're having an affair?
- Oh, I know they are.

00:36.408 --> 00:38.242
I need to catch her
in the unholy act

00:38.276 --> 00:40.744
so she will be crushed
and I will win.

00:40.779 --> 00:42.913
Carter killed Alejandro.

00:42.948 --> 00:45.516
That might not be
how the rest of us remember it.

00:45.550 --> 00:47.718
Kind of pathetic,
don't you think...

00:47.752 --> 00:48.852
Screwing the help?

00:48.887 --> 00:49.887
Hey, you're out of line.

00:49.921 --> 00:51.488
He's trying
to take you away from me.

00:51.523 --> 00:53.324
He doesn't love you like I do.

00:53.358 --> 00:54.992
I don't want to go back home.

00:55.026 --> 00:56.327
Well, for obvious reasons,

00:56.361 --> 00:57.928
I can't let you
stay here anymore.

00:57.963 --> 00:59.330
Well, you need something

00:59.364 --> 01:01.632
to take your mind off
all this drama with Ty.

01:01.666 --> 01:04.668
And a fabulous show-biz party
is just what the doctor ordered.

01:04.703 --> 01:05.936
You doing okay?

01:05.971 --> 01:07.571
I'm just glad he's gone.

01:11.109 --> 01:14.311
Oh, thanks, Zoila,
but I can't Friday.

01:14.346 --> 01:17.348
Spence is having a party for
the cast and crew of his show.

01:17.382 --> 01:18.415
Yeah.

01:18.450 --> 01:20.484
Can we get together tomorrow?

01:20.518 --> 01:21.719
Okay.

01:24.289 --> 01:26.991
Hold on.
I have to call you back.

01:34.532 --> 01:36.166
Carmen, what a small world.

01:36.201 --> 01:38.402
Are you following me?
Why would you think that?

01:38.436 --> 01:40.437
'Cause I also saw you
at the market this morning.

01:40.472 --> 01:42.673
Oh. And at the
movies last night.

01:42.707 --> 01:45.342
What do you think you're doing?
Okay.

01:45.377 --> 01:47.511
Yes, I-I've been waiting for
the right time to talk to you,

01:47.545 --> 01:49.713
but just to help you understand
how I feel.

01:49.748 --> 01:52.483
It doesn't matter how you feel.
I don't feel anything.

01:52.517 --> 01:54.685
- Carmen.
- I date men.

01:54.719 --> 01:57.021
And I'm sorry, Ty,
but all I see when I look at you

01:57.055 --> 01:58.889
is a confused little boy.

01:58.923 --> 02:01.425
Now, stop following me!

02:05.797 --> 02:07.765
What are we doing here, Ty?

02:07.799 --> 02:09.967
I thought we weren't gonna hang
for a while.

02:10.001 --> 02:11.502
This is sort of an emergency.

02:11.536 --> 02:13.170
Have you been reading
the papers, man?

02:13.204 --> 02:14.304
The cops asked the FBI

02:14.339 --> 02:16.140
to help find out who's doing
the home invasions.

02:16.174 --> 02:19.143
The FBI! Okay?
We can't be seen together.

02:19.177 --> 02:21.845
Clearly we're all still freaked
out over what happened, so...

02:21.880 --> 02:24.481
Fine.
I'll get to the point.

02:24.516 --> 02:27.117
I want us to hit another house.

02:27.152 --> 02:28.685
Are you high?

02:28.720 --> 02:30.354
Last time we went out,
Carter killed somebody.

02:30.388 --> 02:32.289
Hey, was I the moron who put
real bullets in the gun?

02:32.323 --> 02:34.958
- No one told you to point it at...
- Shut up, both of you!

02:34.993 --> 02:38.262
Our Robin hood days are over.

02:38.296 --> 02:41.165
No, they're not.
And here's why.

02:42.934 --> 02:46.003
I will go to the cops
and turn us all in

02:46.037 --> 02:47.471
if you don't help me.

02:49.307 --> 02:50.507
You're crazy.

02:50.542 --> 02:52.276
So the doctors tell me.

02:52.310 --> 02:55.779
Every cop in the city
is on alert.

02:55.814 --> 02:58.549
One more house.

02:58.583 --> 03:00.751
If you help me do this,
we're golden.

03:04.622 --> 03:08.459
Let's say we put the masks on
one more time.

03:08.493 --> 03:10.394
Who would we be robbing?

03:10.428 --> 03:12.496
My Uncle Spence.

03:16.067 --> 03:19.069
<b>- sync and corrections by Zac -
- www.addic7ed.com -</b>

03:27.912 --> 03:29.646
What did the doctor say?

03:29.681 --> 03:32.850
I'm not a match.
I'm so sorry.

03:32.884 --> 03:35.085
It's all right, darling.

03:35.120 --> 03:37.254
I'll just get a kidney
from someone else.

03:37.288 --> 03:38.856
Maybe I should get tested.

03:38.890 --> 03:40.557
You're sweet to offer,

03:40.592 --> 03:43.293
but I know how much Tequila
you put away on the weekends.

03:43.328 --> 03:46.063
I'd prefer to have a kidney
that wasn't so abused.

03:46.097 --> 03:48.398
For the record, I drink Tequila
on the weekends

03:48.433 --> 03:50.334
because I spend my weekdays
with you.

03:51.970 --> 03:53.837
Why not call one of our cousins
from Oklahoma?

03:53.872 --> 03:54.838
They might be a match.

03:54.873 --> 03:56.607
I detest that part
of the family.

03:56.641 --> 03:58.542
If I let them give me
a major organ,

03:58.576 --> 04:00.310
they'll think
they have the right

04:00.345 --> 04:01.712
to visit me and use my pool.

04:01.746 --> 04:03.714
Mom, this is your health
that we're talking about.

04:03.748 --> 04:07.551
I just think it would be easier
to buy one from a stranger.

04:07.585 --> 04:09.253
Zoila.

04:09.287 --> 04:11.355
You must know someone who's
strapped for cash in the barrio.

04:11.389 --> 04:13.590
<i>Santo dios.</i>

04:13.625 --> 04:16.192
Oh, good.
Give him a call.

04:16.226 --> 04:18.813
Mom, people aren't allowed
to sell their organs.

04:18.848 --> 04:19.596
Why?

04:19.630 --> 04:22.633
Poor people have organs.
Rich people need them.

04:22.667 --> 04:23.867
Why must the government

04:23.902 --> 04:25.836
always stand in the way
of the small businessman?

04:27.305 --> 04:29.806
Hey, why don't we
call Uncle Henri? No.

04:29.841 --> 04:32.843
I don't want anyone in
the family knowing about this.

04:32.877 --> 04:35.846
Promise me you won't say anything.
Okay.

04:35.880 --> 04:38.282
But you have to start taking
this thing seriously, mom.

04:38.316 --> 04:40.484
I mean, what are we gonna do
if your kidneys fail completely?

04:40.518 --> 04:42.019
Relax.

04:42.053 --> 04:44.054
I gave up food in the '80s.

04:44.088 --> 04:47.157
I see no reason why I can't
give up fluids, as well.

04:50.895 --> 04:52.629
Give me Henri's number.

04:52.664 --> 04:54.731
I just promised mom
I wouldn't call him.

04:54.766 --> 04:56.366
<i>Yeah, but I didn't.</i>

05:00.972 --> 05:03.473
I will be making a decision
about a nurse very soon.

05:03.508 --> 05:05.842
My husband gets home
from the hospital on Friday.

05:05.877 --> 05:08.345
You must be so excited.
I am.

05:08.379 --> 05:10.013
But it won't be
a quick recovery,

05:10.048 --> 05:12.482
so I'm going to need someone
who can...

05:12.517 --> 05:14.384
Put him at ease,
lift his spirits.

05:14.419 --> 05:16.820
I can do that.

05:16.854 --> 05:18.422
Uh-huh.

05:18.456 --> 05:20.257
Well, I have someone else
waiting to be interviewed, so...

05:22.794 --> 05:25.162
Somebody get me a jacket.

05:25.196 --> 05:28.465
'Cause that lady is frosty!

05:28.499 --> 05:31.101
Hi.
Sorry to keep you waiting.

05:31.135 --> 05:34.638
I'm sorry to eavesdrop,
but miss congeniality was loud.

05:34.672 --> 05:37.174
Oh, was that too catty?

05:37.208 --> 05:39.409
Shoot! Now you know I'm a bitch.
Name's Molly.

05:39.444 --> 05:41.612
Marisol.
Please, sit down.

05:41.646 --> 05:44.047
- Nice to meet you.
- Oh, I hope so.

05:44.082 --> 05:46.984
The last lady I worked for,
she said I was too brassy.

05:47.018 --> 05:48.418
I think I'm just fun,

05:48.453 --> 05:50.787
but she was the one
with lupus, so...

05:50.822 --> 05:52.356
Well, I think
you're delightful.

05:52.390 --> 05:55.092
And I'm ready to have someone
working here who makes me laugh.

05:55.126 --> 05:58.729
I recently parted ways
with a very nasty employee.

05:58.763 --> 06:02.320
Fought the urge to kick her
several times a day.

06:02.355 --> 06:03.136
Really?

06:03.171 --> 06:05.202
Shoot.
Now you know I'm a bitch.

06:05.236 --> 06:08.538
Self-deprecating.
I love that.

06:08.573 --> 06:11.275
Here is my resumee
and my references.

06:11.309 --> 06:15.245
So, cards on the table,
I really want this job.

06:15.280 --> 06:18.348
You just seem so nice,
and I love the way you dress.

06:18.383 --> 06:20.150
And if there's anything
you want to know about me,

06:20.184 --> 06:21.518
just go ahead and ask.

06:21.552 --> 06:25.122
Well, I do have one question.

06:25.156 --> 06:26.823
When can you start?

06:32.563 --> 06:34.731
Adrian, have you seem the paper?

06:34.766 --> 06:37.034
Nicholas Deering was hit
by a car.

06:37.068 --> 06:38.435
We should run over there later

06:38.469 --> 06:40.604
and drop off
some sort of bouquet.

06:40.638 --> 06:42.806
Marisol is allergic to roses,

06:42.840 --> 06:46.343
so... that seems
the logical choice.

06:47.612 --> 06:49.379
What's wrong?

06:49.414 --> 06:51.515
I know you're sleeping with Tony.

06:53.685 --> 06:54.751
So?

06:54.786 --> 06:57.087
So, you have to stop
seeing him.

06:57.121 --> 06:59.856
Mm... I'd rather not.

06:59.891 --> 07:01.325
Evelyn!

07:01.359 --> 07:02.526
Tony makes me happy.

07:02.560 --> 07:04.861
And as it turns out,
I like to be happy.

07:04.896 --> 07:06.029
What am I supposed to do?

07:06.064 --> 07:07.531
Just stand here
while you screw the help?

07:07.565 --> 07:10.567
<i>Isn't that where I stood
while you screwed the help?</i>

07:10.601 --> 07:12.836
That was different.
How?

07:12.870 --> 07:15.238
I don't know.

07:15.273 --> 07:16.540
Don't worry.

07:16.574 --> 07:18.675
Lots of people have
open marriages these days.

07:18.710 --> 07:21.078
I'm sure you will find a way
to adjust.

07:21.112 --> 07:22.412
And if it will cheer you up,

07:22.447 --> 07:23.847
I'll let you try to seduce
Valentina.

07:23.881 --> 07:24.981
She'll probably quit,

07:25.016 --> 07:27.684
but her cleaning is subpar,
so I won't care.

07:27.719 --> 07:30.454
Why would Tony want to be
with you?

07:30.488 --> 07:31.855
He finds me attractive.

07:31.889 --> 07:33.557
Which part?

07:33.591 --> 07:34.958
Your vicious tongue?

07:34.992 --> 07:36.693
Your acidic personality?

07:36.728 --> 07:40.063
Or that ice cube that lies
where your heart ought to be?

07:40.098 --> 07:42.232
You finished trying
to hurt me now?

07:42.266 --> 07:44.568
You misunderstand me.

07:44.602 --> 07:47.571
I'm saying only a man like me

07:47.605 --> 07:51.742
can be attracted
to a woman like you.

07:57.615 --> 08:02.152
S-semi annual
c-clearance sale.

08:02.186 --> 08:04.388
Very good,
Mr. Kenneth.

08:04.422 --> 08:07.124
What's going on? Rosie's using the
coupons that come in the mail

08:07.158 --> 08:09.459
to help Uncle Ken
do his speech therapy.

08:09.494 --> 08:13.430
20 p-percent off shoes.

08:13.464 --> 08:15.031
Wonderful!

08:15.066 --> 08:17.634
And I'll take that.

08:17.668 --> 08:20.804
Reg, I saw you left a bag
in Lucinda's room.

08:20.838 --> 08:22.272
Are you planning on staying
with us?

08:22.306 --> 08:24.274
Just for a couple days.
My apartment's being painted.

08:24.308 --> 08:26.676
Really?
'Cause I ran into Althea,

08:26.677 --> 08:29.045
and she says you don't
live there anymore.

08:29.046 --> 08:31.214
Your friend has no idea
what she's talking about.

08:34.352 --> 08:37.187
Well, I never knew her
to make stuff up.

08:37.221 --> 08:38.655
Hello?

08:38.688 --> 08:40.690
Let me get her.

08:40.725 --> 08:44.327
Mm.
It's Dr. Sanders.

08:44.362 --> 08:48.031
Oh, why would he be calling me?
Thank you.

08:48.065 --> 08:51.835
This is Didi Miller.

08:51.869 --> 08:54.404
Well, I'm very sorry, doctor,
but my husband is doing better,

08:54.439 --> 08:57.174
and we no longer require
your services.

08:57.208 --> 08:59.309
Why is he calling you?

08:59.343 --> 09:02.045
It's nothing.
Got to run. See y'all later.

09:02.079 --> 09:04.347
You said
you stopped seeing him.

09:04.382 --> 09:06.883
We'll talk about it later,
Rosie!

09:06.918 --> 09:10.554
We sure will.

09:10.588 --> 09:13.790
What do you mean you told him?

09:13.825 --> 09:16.593
I mean Adrian confronted me
about the affair,

09:16.627 --> 09:17.661
and I confessed.

09:17.695 --> 09:20.664
W-why would you do that?

09:20.698 --> 09:22.833
Because I adore you,

09:22.867 --> 09:24.801
and I'm sick of sneak around
in the shadows.

09:24.836 --> 09:27.170
Our relationship needs the sun
in order to grow.

09:27.205 --> 09:30.173
How did Mr. Powell react?

09:30.208 --> 09:31.908
There were
a few barbed remarks,

09:31.943 --> 09:33.810
but not much in the way
of emotion.

09:33.845 --> 09:35.812
We are jaded sophisticates,
after all.

09:35.847 --> 09:37.647
Tony?

09:37.682 --> 09:40.650
Why aren't you smiling?
This is good news.

09:40.685 --> 09:42.385
Of course.

09:44.489 --> 09:46.590
This is a wonderful thing.

09:46.624 --> 09:48.525
I have an idea.

09:48.559 --> 09:51.161
Tonight, when we make love,
let's leave the door open.

09:51.195 --> 09:52.562
Why?

09:52.597 --> 09:54.331
Adrian's never heard me orgasm
before.

09:54.365 --> 09:55.966
I thought
it might be instructive.

09:57.735 --> 09:59.569
That was a joke.

09:59.604 --> 10:01.171
Why aren't you laughing?

10:01.205 --> 10:03.073
I'm sorry.

10:03.107 --> 10:07.944
It's just... I really never
thought you'd tell him.

